While I&#39;ve been pretty busy for the last month, I did find time to do the [Ludum Dare](https://ldjam.com/) last weekend. I worked on a team with Aaron Aaeng and Kevin Yang to make [&quot;uP-8: Microprocessor&quot;](https://schmaron.itch.io/up-8) in 72 hours!

uP-8 is a game where you program real assembly to control a rover and solve puzzles. It even comes with a 20-page User Assembly Language Guide. I ended up being the only programmer on the project, with Aaron working on writing and level design, and Kevin working on Art.

I also did the graphics work, and I am pretty proud of it (I think the CRT effect really sells the aesthetic).

You can download the game for Windows, Mac, and Linux at [itch.io](https://schmaron.itch.io/up-8).

And, if you want, you can view our [Ludum Dare game post](https://ldjam.com/events/ludum-dare/38/%2416171).
